<br>
It was a HUGE change to my offensive/defensive skills.  Seriously, it's hard to even describe.  I hang out in the Grey sometimes soloing.  I get an add, I root it, move away and continue to fight the one on my pet.  Every 40 sec or so, I root it again.  Sometimes I get another add.  I root him too.  Pet kills first mob, moves to 2nd.  Another mob adds.  So now I'm keeping two rooted and chaining pets on the main.  <br>
<br>
Am I stressed?  Not at all.  It's TOTALLY easy to keep them in place.  Adding root was HUGE!<br>
<br>
Now about the root/DD thing.  Yep, I have done it.  I did it in Akheva the other day.  My earring casts root fast enough to root them before they can get to me.  It took forever to burn them down, using a pet was WAY better.  I think it was like 12 Boots of Blade calling nukes with no pet.  And 2 SoFB nukes with a pet.  The root DD thing is possible, but it sucks.<br>
<br>
Root has been usefull in groups too, especially in dungeons when mobs run.  I have played &quot;chanter&quot; a few times in groups too.  Even in the arena in Kael.  Root a giant, malosini to make it stick better, then keep him rooted while my group kills another.<br>
<br>
